==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shadowing
<hw>Shad"ow*ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Shade, or gradation
of light and color; shading.</def> <rj><au>Feltham.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A faint representation; an adumbration.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There are . . . in savage theology <qex>shadowings</qex>, quaint
or majestic, of the conception of a Supreme Deity.</q>
<rj><qau>Tylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shadowish</ent>⟦br⟧
